Stoeger’s new Double Defense side-by-side shotgun is a straightforward, rugged and reliable home defense shotgun. postcontent:
What an unfortunate ordeal. I am listing this excellent firearm that hammers out 3 catastrophic cartridges: 410 shot, 45 Long Colt, and the ominous .454 casull big game round. With a wide variety a buckshot available for this very type of firearm, including 000 buckshot (essentially throwing 4 9mm sized projectiles downrange with each pull of the trigger for all 6 rounds in the cylinder) and the ability to make the devastating yet economical wax/birdshot slugs, you will be well prepared for any encounter with this strapped tightly to your thigh. The very sight of this weapon would surely make any home intruder soil his shorts, so remember to politely ask the intruder to leave before flicking on the lights otherwise you'll have a smelly mess to clean up on your living room floor. Upon seeing your stainless steel Raging Judge Magnum, the intruder will commence to beg for mercy, compliment you on your taste in firearms, and attempt to allign with you as an ally in the event of an "End of Days" scenario. Beware of profuse compliments that will inundate you upon taking ownership of this weapon. A mere 20 rounds have been fired in this hand cannon, and I have thoroughly cleaned and polished each cylinder with Breakfree Cleaner Lubricant Preservative. MSRP from Taurus is over 1000 dollars on this elephant revolver. It is no longer in production. The only reason I'm selling is to try to get out of credit card debt. title: For Sale/Trade:  Para Ordnace Tactical Rifle
postcontent:
Factory new in the box with Para hard case, all packaging (including serial numbered box), manual and one (still sealed) original Para 30 round magazine (uses standard M16/M4 mags).  The Para USA Tactical Target Rifle, TTR-XA is a semi-automatic rifle that’s made in the U.S.A, 5.56mm caliber (can also fire .223 ammo) and features a 16.5" chrome lined barrel, a Rapid Deployment Stock (RDS) (LOP adjustable from 11 3/4" to 14 3/8") and an overall length 34 3/4" to 38" (27 3/4" with stock folded).  One of the great things about this rifle, is the Delayed Impingement Gas System (DIGS), which puts the recoil system up front, above the barrel, which pushes the muzzle back down for quicker follow up shots and reduced felt recoil.  Because of the DIGS, the rifle can be fired with the stock folded and the stock locks up nice and tight!  not only does it have a full length Picatinney rail at the 12 o’clock position and full length forearm rails at the 3, 6 and 9 positions.

The rifle also features a Manifold Injection System (MIS), which expels gases through the bolt carrier, making this the cleanest running auto-loading rifle in the world, plus it can be field stripped with not tools.  These rifles were manufactured by Para USA in Charlotte, NC.  This is the high end model and rarest of the three models Para made. By manufacturing this limited series, Ceská zbrojovka is referring back to the break of 1960´s and 1970´s, when the trestle board of design engineer František Koucký saw the evolution of the first draft of the famous “seventy-five“. There have been numerous pieces of the first model of CZ 75 preserved all over the World, excluding the cock safety lug and shorter frame and slide grooves. These pistols now represent unique vintage pieces held in private collections. With the limited series of 525 pcs of 75th Anniversary, Ceská zbrojovka is offering the option for purchase of this legend even in the year 2011, which is approximately 40 years since its evolution and 30 years following its upgrade to CZ 75B.
